				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Operation Cedar Falls: A Black Sun Operational Campaign" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>On January 8th, 1967 American lead forces jumped off on the largest American ground operation of the Vietnam War. It would last 20 days. The operation had been planned to remove the Viet Cong threat from an area north of Saigon known as the Iron Triangle. This area, only about 155 square km in size, was a major stronghold of the Viet Cong.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This 15 page PDF uses the BLACK SUN skirmish rules in a strictly historical operation led by US Army forces in the Iron Triangle area of Vietnam. It adds larger game play elements to the Black Sun universe. Provided are new Force Cards, New &amp;quot;What the...?!&amp;quot; Cards (ready to be printed and played with) and a three scenario campaign that can be enjoyed by multiple players.It also provides new rules including a Forward Observer and mortar team, starting fires and a Scenario Point objective system to determine the winner of a multi scenario campaign.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This Operational Campaign utilizes Platoon size units for game play and is designed for advanced Black Sun players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
